text.tspan: COORD Array of NBC byte float with NCOORD elements
where COORD is (topX, topY, topZ, baseX, baseY, baseZ)
offset= 36 + NCOORD * NBC + NZCORN * NBZ + NACTNUM*NBA + 13
ncol, nrow, nlay, xshift, yshift, zshift,
ZCORN array of NBZ byte float with NZCORN elements where each
corner pillar has 4 values; when unrotated: (SW, SE, NW, NE)
ACTNUM array of NBA byte INT with NACTNUM elements, where ACTNUM
is usually 0 or 1 per cell for NACTNUM = (NCOL * NROW * NLAY), C order.
Format for 3D geometry for reduced Corner Point Grids
Reduced Corner Point: ZCORN is only defined for top cells except for
NLAY + 1. I.e. ZCORN split/overlap as in Eclipse GRDECL is not possible.
441: COORD 4 byte float, ZCORN 4byte float, ACTNUM 1byte sign INT
841: A.a. but COORD is 8 byte Float.
881: A.a. but both COORD and ZCORN are 8 byte float
xshift/yshift/zshift are usually 0.0 and xscale/yscale/zscale are usually
1.0. For format 441, use of xshift and yshift is recommended to maintain
Default is left-handed system with corner (0,0,0) in lower, left,
Z is positive downwards, Y is North given no rotation.
